premise_source_doc_sentence: In common use the term is used to describe the largest species from this family , especially those of the genus Macropus : the red kangaroo , antilopine kangaroo , eastern grey kangaroo , and western grey kangaroo .

The kangaroo mice are closely related to the kangaroo rats , which belong to the same subfamily , Dipodomyinae .
The pale kangaroo mouse burrows only in fine sand , while the dark kangaroo mouse prefers fine , gravelly soils but may also burrow in sand or sandy soil .
As with the terms `` wallaroo '' and `` wallaby '' , `` kangaroo '' refers to a polyphyletic grouping of species .
